OL,3,COne in eight women victims of domestic
OL,4,Cabuse, stalking or sexual assault
OL,6,FOne in eight women were victims of
OL,7,Fdomestic crime, sexual abuse or
OL,8,Fstalking in the last year, new data
OL,9,Fhas revealed.
OL,11,FAccording to the Office for National
OL,12,FStatistics (ONS), around 3.2 million
OL,13,Fwomen aged over 16 were victims of at
OL,14,Fleast one of these crimes between
OL,15,FMarch 2024 and 2025.
OL,17,FIt is the first time the ONS has
OL,18,Fgrouped domestic abuse, sexual assault
OL,19,Fand stalking figures together, using
OL,20,Fdata collected as part of the Crime
OL,21,FSurvey for England and Wales.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
