OL,6,FWomen's Aid welcomed the ONS grouping
OL,7,Fthe data together, saying it was a
OL,8,Fstep towards a better overview of
OL,9,Fthese crimes.
OL,11,FSarah Davidge, head of research and
OL,12,Fevaluation at Women's Aid, said the
OL,13,Fmove "reflects the Government's
OL,14,Fcommitment to ending VAWG", but added
OL,15,Fthe data does not show the number of
OL,16,Ftimes each person was victimised.
