OL,3,COne in eight women victims of domestic
OL,4,Cabuse, stalking or sexual assault
OL,6,FShe added: "We know that women
OL,7,Fencounter higher rates of repeat
OL,8,Fvictimisation, are more likely to be
OL,9,Fsubject to coercive and controlling
OL,10,Fbehaviour and be seriously harmed or
OL,11,Fkilled than male victims.
OL,13,F"Therefore, prevalence measures can
OL,14,Funderestimate the gender asymmetry of
OL,15,Fthese crimes."
