OL,6,FElsewhere, ONS data published on
OL,7,FThursday shows people aged 16 and over
OL,8,Fexperienced 9.4 million incidents of
OL,9,Fcrime in the year to March 2025, up
OL,10,Ffrom 8.8 million in the previous 12
OL,11,Fmonths.
OL,13,FThe rise is mainly due to a 31% rise
OL,14,Fin fraud, which accounts for 4.2
OL,15,Fmillion incidents and is the highest
OL,16,Festimate since fraud was first
OL,17,Fmeasured in the survey in 2016/17.
